"```sql\nSELECT COUNT(DISTINCT Examination.ID)\nFROM Examination\nJOIN Patient ON Examination.ID = Patient.ID\nJOIN Laboratory ON Patient.ID = Laboratory.ID\nWHERE Examination.Diagnosis = 'SLE'\nAND (Laboratory.SSB = 'negative' OR Laboratory.SSB = '0');\n```\n\nThis SQL query counts the number of distinct patients who have a normal anti-SSB result and are diagnosed with SLE in the examination. It joins the `Examination`, `Patient`, and `Laboratory` tables using the foreign key relationships and applies the conditions specified in the evidence."